main event: Mr. Maynard J. Weber reported sighting an unidentified object while working at Copper Brite Cleaners in Los Angeles on 14 March 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as having a blunt nose with a square pod behind it and a dome on top and bottom., The size of the object appeared elongated when viewed in relation to the moon in the photograph., The observation occurred around 2130-2200 PST during the last full moon., Photographs were taken with a camera featuring a 2000mm lens., The report indicated there was no trail or exhaust seen from the object.
witness description: Mr. Maynard J. Weber, 41, a resident of Los Angeles
